[assistant] Fixed the missing `picocli` runtime dependency for the Liquibase launcher test.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - `tests/src/org.liquibase/liquibase-core/4.17.0/build.gradle`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] 
[assistant] ```gradle
[assistant] testImplementation 'info.picocli:picocli:4.6.3'
[assistant] ```
[assistant] 
[assistant] Why:
[assistant] 
[assistant] `LiquibaseLauncherTest` invokes `LiquibaseLauncher.main(...)`, which loads `LiquibaseCommandLine`. In Liquibase `4.17.0`, `LiquibaseCommandLine` references `picocli.CommandLine$IFactory`, but `liquibase-core`’s published POM does not bring in `picocli`. Since the build-local `LIQUIBASE_HOME/internal/lib` is populated from `testRuntimeClasspath`, adding the correct test dependency also makes the launcher’s isolated classloader able to resolve `picocli`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] No metadata files were modified.
[assistant-event] text_end
